│ THOUGHT: The miscompile occurs when foldBitCeil removes the guarding select and propagates poison from ctlz due to a range that excludes zero. Alive2 shows the ctlz result │
│ has attached MD_range metadata. To prevent this specific issue without breaking other expected folds, I will add a conservative bailout: if the matched ctlz instruction    │
│ has MD_range metadata, skip the transformation. This avoids the poison propagation while preserving other cases (e.g., return range including zero).                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ sed -i '3496a \ \ \ \ // Bail out if ctlz result has range metadata; folding may propagate poison.\n \ \ \ \ if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Ctlz))\n \ \ \ \ \ \ if    │
│ (I->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range))\n \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ return nullptr;' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp && submit-patch                            │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                         │
